{
  "id": "seroperson_jvm-live-reload_38",
  "repo_name": "seroperson/jvm-live-reload",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/seroperson/jvm-live-reload",
  "base_commit": "3a36b8f8038e804db55c25fdd3edeb698bcce7df",
  "pr_number": 38,
  "issue_number": 25,
  "issue_title": "Critical: Concurrent first requests can bypass startup health checks and return 503",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\nThe HTTP proxy can serve concurrent requests before the target application has passed `RestApiHealthCheckStartupHook`.\n\nWhen two requests arrive during first startup or reload:\n\n1. Request A receives a `ReloadGeneration`, starts the app, and waits for the startup health hook.\n2. Request B concurrently calls `reload()`, receives `null`, skips startup waiting, and immediately proxies to the target port.\n3. The target app is not listening yet, so Request B gets `503`.\n\nThis breaks the live-reload readiness guarantee under normal browser behavior, because browsers commonly issue concurrent requests for HTML, JS, CSS, images, and API calls.\n\nSearches checked included `concurrent startup`, `health-check concurrent`, `503 startup reload`, and `RestApiHealthCheckStartupHook`.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Build the project locally.\n\n```bash\n./gradlew --no-configuration-cache -q :core:webserver:classes\n```\n\n2. Start an HTTP live-reload proxy with `RestApiHealthCheckStartupHook`.\n\n3. Use a target app that delays binding its HTTP port for 2 seconds.\n\n4. Send two concurrent requests to the proxy during first startup.\n\n5. Observe one request passing after health check, while another request proxies early and fails.\n\n## Actual Result\n\nOne concurrent request returned `503` before the app became healthy.\n\nValidated terminal output:\n\n```text\nBUILDLINK returning generation 1\nINFO \ud83d\udd03 Reloading an application\nBUILDLINK returning null\nDEBUG No change in the application classes\nDEBUG Request successfully handled in ReloadHandler. Was reloaded: false\nDEBUG Creating a new proxy connection for path /greet\n\nINFO \ud83d\ude80 Starting SlowApp\nSlowApp main entered; delaying bind\nDEBUG Running RestApiHealthCheckStartupHook\nDEBUG Waiting for the health-check to return success ...\n\nERROR Error during connection\njava.net.ConnectException: Connection refused\n\nFIRST_RESULT 503 body='' tookMs=645\n\nSlowApp listening on localhost:19091\nDEBUG RestApiHealthCheckStartupHook took 2348ms\nDEBUG Finished reloading\nSECOND_RESULT 200 body='hello' tookMs=2550\n```\n\n## Expected Result\n\nAll requests arriving during startup/reload should wait for the same startup lifecycle to complete before proxying to the target app.\n\nNo request should bypass the startup health hook and hit the target before readiness.\n\n## Evidence\n\nEnvironment:\n\n```text\nOpenJDK 17.0.18\njust 1.51.0\nScala CLI 1.14.0\n```\n\nBuild validation:\n\n```text\n./gradlew --no-configuration-cache -q :core:webserver:classes\n```\n\nRuntime validation:\n\n```text\nFIRST_RESULT 503 body='' tookMs=645\nSECOND_RESULT 200 body='hello' tookMs=2550\n```\n\nCleanup check:\n\n```text\nNo process remained listening on :19090 or :19091 after the run.\n```\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`ReloadHandler` calls `server.reload()` per request, then immediately proxies:\n\n[ReloadHandler.java](https://github.com/seroperson/jvm-live-reload/core/webserver/src/main/java/me/seroperson/reload/live/webserver/ReloadHandler.java):27\n\n`BaseDevServerStart.reload()` is not synchronized end-to-end. Only `startInternal()` is synchronized:\n\n[BaseDevServerStart.java](https://github.com/seroperson/jvm-live-reload/core/build-link/src/main/java/me/seroperson/reload/live/BaseDevServerStart.java):199\n\n`DevServerReloader` sets `currentApplicationClassLoader` before the application has actually started and before startup hooks finish:\n\n[DevServerReloader.java](https://github.com/seroperson/jvm-live-reload/core/runner/src/main/java/me/seroperson/reload/live/runner/DevServerReloader.java):121\n\nThe startup hook runs only after the application thread starts:\n\n[BaseDevServerStart.java](https://github.com/seroperson/jvm-live-reload/core/build-link/src/main/java/me/seroperson/reload/live/BaseDevServerStart.java):140\n\nSo concurrent requests can observe \u201cno change\u201d and proxy while another request is still running startup hooks.\n\n## Security/Business Impact\n\nThis causes flaky dev-server behavior under normal browser traffic. A browser loading a page can issue concurrent requests during first startup or reload, causing random assets/API calls to fail with `503`.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Broken page loads during live reload.\n- Flaky developer workflows.\n- Misleading backend errors even when the application starts correctly.\n- The readiness hook does not reliably protect all requests.\n\n## Suggested Fix\n\nSerialize the startup/reload readiness lifecycle.\n\nRecommended options:\n\n1. Make `BaseDevServerStart.reload()` synchronize the full flow from `buildLink.reload()` through `startInternal()` and startup hooks.\n2. Track an `isStarting` / `startupFuture` state so concurrent requests wait for the in-progress startup instead of proxying.\n3. Add a regression test with two concurrent first requests against a delayed target app, asserting both return `200` instead of one returning `503`.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-23T09:02:06.000Z",
